{"id":"edgar-allan-poe","files":[{"path":"ATTRIBUTION.md","encoding":"utf8","data":"# Image and research attribution\n\nEdgar Allan Poe portrait, public-domain historical photograph via Wikimedia Commons\nSpecial:FilePath.\n\nEach lesson uses a distinct remote image and includes a research source link in its notes. The\nremote images are not redistributed in this source package; the reader displays them when connected\nand preserves the local SVG cover offline. Verify current reuse details at each linked Wikimedia\nCommons file page before commercial redistribution.\n\n- **A Restless Life** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Edgar_Allan_Poe_2_retouched_and_transparent_bg.png;\n  research source: https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/edgar-allan-poe\n- **Magazines and Audiences** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Graham%27s_Magazine_January_1852.jpg; research\n  source: https://www.loc.gov/item/today-in-history/january-19/\n- **Sound in Poetry** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/The_Raven_Illustration_John_Tenniel.jpg;\n  research source: https://www.poetryfoundation.org/articles/69390/the-philosophy-of-composition\n- **Unreliable Voices** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Edgar_Allan_Poe_house_in_Baltimore.jpg;\n  research source: https://poemuseum.org/poes-complete-works/\n- **Gothic Pressure** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Poe%27s_house_in_Baltimore.jpg; research\n  source: https://poemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/Educator-Resource-Packet.pdf\n- **Dupin’s Method** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/The_Murders_in_the_Rue_Morgue_illustration.jpg;\n  research source: https://poemuseum.org/tag/short-story/\n"},{"path":"assets/images/cover.svg","encoding":"utf8","data":"<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\"><rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#756d68\"/><path d=\"M0 680 C300 520 560 800 900 620 S1320 440 1600 600 V900 H0Z\" fill=\"#f6f4ef\" opacity=\".16\"/><circle cx=\"1280\" cy=\"200\" r=\"138\" fill=\"#f6f4ef\" opacity=\".24\"/><text x=\"110\" y=\"360\" fill=\"#f6f4ef\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\" font-size=\"78\">Edgar Allan Poe: Sound, Shadow, and Story</text><text x=\"115\" y=\"435\" fill=\"#f6f4ef\" font-family=\"Arial,sans-serif\" font-size=\"30\" opacity=\".84\">An MCF 1.0 course</text></svg>"},{"path":"chapters/craft-and-form/chapter.yaml","encoding":"utf8","data":"id: craft-and-form\ntitle: \"Craft and Form\"\ndescription: \"A focused unit in Edgar Allan Poe: Sound, Shadow, and Story.\"\nlessons:\n  - lessons/01-sound-in-poetry.mcf\n  - lessons/02-unreliable-voices.mcf\n"},{"path":"chapters/craft-and-form/lessons/01-sound-in-poetry.mcf","encoding":"base64","data":""},{"path":"chapters/craft-and-form/lessons/02-unreliable-voices.mcf","encoding":"base64","data":""},{"path":"chapters/gothic-and-detective/chapter.yaml","encoding":"utf8","data":"id: gothic-and-detective\ntitle: \"Gothic and Detective Fiction\"\ndescription: \"A focused unit in Edgar Allan Poe: Sound, Shadow, and Story.\"\nlessons:\n  - lessons/01-gothic-pressure.mcf\n  - lessons/02-dupin-s-method.mcf\n"},{"path":"chapters/gothic-and-detective/lessons/01-gothic-pressure.mcf","encoding":"base64","data":""},{"path":"chapters/gothic-and-detective/lessons/02-dupin-s-method.mcf","encoding":"base64","data":""},{"path":"chapters/life-and-context/chapter.yaml","encoding":"utf8","data":"id: life-and-context\ntitle: \"Life and Context\"\ndescription: \"A focused unit in Edgar Allan Poe: Sound, Shadow, and Story.\"\nlessons:\n  - lessons/01-a-restless-life.mcf\n  - lessons/02-magazines-and-audiences.mcf\n"},{"path":"chapters/life-and-context/lessons/01-a-restless-life.mcf","encoding":"base64","data":""},{"path":"chapters/life-and-context/lessons/02-magazines-and-audiences.mcf","encoding":"base64","data":""},{"path":"manif